      <!-- Hero / Intro -->
      <section class="hero" id="hero">
        <div class="ambient" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="swirl" style="top:8%; left:18%; animation-delay:0s;"></div>
          <div class="swirl" style="top:60%; left:70%; animation-delay:4s;"></div>
          <div class="swirl" style="top:75%; left:35%; animation-delay:7s;"></div>
        </div>

        <h1>Vienna</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">
          A measured waltz of tradition and quiet reinvention—coffee rituals, palace echoes, and
          streets that hum with history yet feel intimate.
        </div>
        <div class="quote">
          “Vienna is the kind of city where even silence moves with grace.” <small>— Local whisper</small>
        </div>
        <div class="quote">
          “Every corner here has a score; you just need to listen.” <small>— Ayushi</small>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Best Time to Visit -->
      <section class="section" id="best-time">
        <h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
        <div class="desc">
          Vienna wears every season like a different composition: spring brings blooming gardens
          and open terraces, summer fills courtyards with music, autumn softens light over baroque
          rooftops, and winter wraps the city in warm candlelit cafes. There’s no single “right”
          time, but if it’s your first visit, late spring (May–June) or early autumn (September)
          offers mild weather, fewer crowds, and a sense of the city unfolding at a gentle tempo.
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="max-width:850px; margin:0 auto; display:flex; gap:20px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div style="flex:1; min-width:220px;">
            <div class="label">Why First-Timers</div>
            <h3 style="margin-top:0; font-size:1.35rem;">Balance & Warmth</h3>
            <p>
              Gardens are in bloom, open-air concerts tease the corners, and the streets feel lived-in
              without overwhelming. It’s a sweet middle ground before the high summer tempo.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div style="flex:1; min-width:220px;">
            <div class="label">Seasonal Notes</div>
            <h3 style="margin-top:0; font-size:1.35rem;">All moods live here</h3>
            <p>
              From winter’s soft glow in coffeehouses to spring’s fresh energy and autumn’s golden
              reflection, Vienna rewards repeat visits with new layers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

